{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>Members of this family include the Bacillus subtilis spore coat protein H (CotH). Assembly of CotH requires both CotE and GerE and is required for the correct assembly of both inner and outer layers of the coat. CotH appears to be a structural component of the coat being localised at the interface of the 2 coat layers [[cite:PUB00035372], [cite:PUB00035373], [cite:PUB00035374]]. Furthermore, CotH has been shown to be an atypical protein kinase. CotH-dependent phosphorylation of CotB and CotG is required for the efficient germination of B. subtilis spores [[cite:PUB00085072]].</p>\n\n<p>This entry also includes CotH2/3/7 from Rhizopus delemar (mucormycosis agent), which promote invasion of host epithelial cells by adhering to receptors on the host cell surface to facilitate endocytosis of the pathogen into host cells [[cite:PUB00099571], [cite:PUB00099572]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "5jda", "name" "Bacillus cereus CotH kinase plus Mg2+/AMP"}, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"panther" {"PTHR40050" "INNER SPORE COAT PROTEIN H"}, "pfam" {"PF08757" "CotH kinase protein"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Spore coat protein CotH/Invasin CotH2/3/7", "short" "Spore_coat_CotH_CotH2/3/7"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 2, "domain_architectures" 1519, "proteomes" 1678, "taxa" 7372, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 20837, "sets" 0, "proteins" 20201, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 11721}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR014867", :literature {"PUB00035372" {"URL" nil, "issue" "3", "authors" ["Giorno R" "Bozue J" "Cote C" "Wenzel T" "Moody KS" "Mallozzi M" "Ryan M" "Wang R" "Zielke R" "Maddock JR" "Friedlander A" "Welkos S" "Driks A."], "ISO_journal" "J. Bacteriol.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1128/JB.00921-06", "me